                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/208</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-26T16:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 19, 4 p.m. and Department’s January 22. Nationalization of
                    petroleum. In accordance with Department’s wishes subject was taken up
                    personally with General Carranza. He informed me this morning: “The Government
                    is not contemplating the issuance of a decree nationalizing the petroleum
                    industry.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
